       <p><h1>Imran Khan</h1><h2> Leadership Style:</h2><h3>:Background:</h3> Former cricketer and captain of the Pakistan national cricket team, philanthropist.
        Political Career: Founded Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf (PTI) in 1996. Became Prime Minister in 2018.
        Focus Areas: Anti-corruption, welfare state model, and reforms in health and education.
      
        
       
        
       

Leadership Style: Charismatic and populist, often emphasizing a new political vision and the fight against corruption.
Governance: Focused on institutional reforms, social welfare programs like Ehsaas Program, and austerity measures.


Economic Policies: Advocated for austerity measures, reducing reliance on foreign loans, and enhancing tax collection. Focused on social welfare and poverty alleviation.
Challenges: Faced economic instability, inflation, and difficulties in implementing reforms.






